<snippet>
	<content><![CDATA[const percentile = (arr, val) =>
  100 * arr.reduce((acc, v) => acc + (v < val ? 1 : 0) + (v === val ? 0.5 : 0), 0) / arr.length;]]></content>
	<description>Uses the percentile formula to calculate how many numbers in the given array are less or equal to the given value.  Use `Array.reduce()` to calculate how many numbers are below the value and how many are the same value and apply the percentile formula.</description>
	<tabTrigger>percentile</tabTrigger>
	<scope>source.js</scope>
</snippet>